{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund free dental care for all under-18s, regardless of NHS dentist availability",
        "additional_details": "We believe this is an educational emergency. The national \"Belonging and Thriving\" agenda fails when children are left in agony. Students cannot learn while suffering chronic pain or sleep deprivation. They cannot \"belong\" when ashamed of their smile or missing school for extractions. For families locked out of the NHS, private fees can be impossible. If the NHS cannot provide a space, the state must fund private care. We must end this two-tier health system.",
        "background": "Guarantee free dental care for all under-18s. Where NHS practices are full, the Government must fund private check-ups and essential treatment. No child should be denied healthcare or left in pain because their parents cannot afford private fees. End the \"dental deserts\" now.",
